Class USB_Config_Descriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.ailis.usb4java.jni.USB_Descriptor_Header
      • de.ailis.usb4java.jni.USB_Config_Descriptor

  • public final class USB_Config_Descriptor
extends USB_Descriptor_Header
    The USB configuration descriptor describes information about a specific USB device configuration.

    Klaus Reimer (k@ailis.de)

      • bmAttributes

        public int bmAttributes()
        Returns a bitmap with configuration attributes.
        • Bit 7: Reserved. (USB 1: Bus-powered)
        • Bit 6: Self-powered.
        • Bit 5: Remote wakeup.
        • Bit 4: Reserved.
        • Bit 3: Reserved.
        • Bit 2: Reserved.
        • Bit 1: Reserved.
        • Bit 0: Reserved.
        Returns:
        A bitmap with configuration attributes (unsigned byte).

      • bMaxPower

        public int bMaxPower()
        Returns the maximum power consumption of the device when this configuration is active and the device is fully operational. The power is expressed in 2 maA units (50 means 100mA for example).
        Returns:
        The maximum power consumption in 2mA units (unsigned byte).

      • extralen

      • iface

        public USB_Interface[] iface()
        Returns the interfaces of this USB configuration. The original method is named "interface" but this can't be used in Java because it is a reserved word.
        Returns:
        The interfaces of this USB configuration.
